name: CustomWebPath
description: CustomWebPath is a helper class that makes creating and attaching custom web nodes to our standard web nodes easier

methods.name: addNode
methods.description: see addNode(Tile, boolean) with default of True

methods.name: addNodes
methods.description: Adds each Tile using addNode(Tile, boolean) with a default of True

methods.name: connectToStart
methods.description: This will connect the start of this path to the provided node index when attachToWeb() or WebFinder.addCustomWebPath(CustomWebPath) is called for this path This will NOT add this path to the full global web.

methods.name: connectStartToClosestNode
methods.description: This will connect the start of this path to the nearest BasicWebNode when attachToWeb() or WebFinder.addCustomWebPath(CustomWebPath) is called for this path This will NOT cadd this path to the full global web.

methods.name: connectEndToClosestNode
methods.description: This will connect the end of this path to the nearest BasicWebNode when attachToWeb() or WebFinder.addCustomWebPath(CustomWebPath) is called Note: This should only be called after all web nodes are added, otherwise it'll attach at the wrong point in your custom path This will NOT add this path to the full global web.

methods.name: connectToEnd
methods.description: This will connect the end of this path to the provided node index when attachToWeb() or WebFinder.addCustomWebPath(CustomWebPath) is called for this path This will NOT connect this path to the full global web

methods.name: attachToWeb
methods.description: Attaches this custom web path into the global web
